{"type":"text","timestamp":1775857444657,"sessionID":"ses_286a6b3f6ffeR9JuYfYvatljVo","part":{"id":"prt_d795a1241001zWsazGS5hWfc5i","messageID":"msg_d7959f552001U5772BpGXusMTp","sessionID":"ses_286a6b3f6ffeR9JuYfYvatljVo","type":"text","text":"**Verification Report: AR-017 PicoD JWT Middleware**\n\n## ⚠️ Spec Mismatch Detected\n\nThe **spec content** provided describes a **Kubernetes client-go library** (for API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), but the actual implementation in `pkg/picod` is a **JWT authentication middleware**.\n\n### What the Spec Describes (client-go):\n- `Clientset` with RuntimeV1alpha1 client\n- `AgentRuntimes` and `CodeInterpreters` typed clients\n- Kubernetes client generation patterns\n\n### What Was Implemented (JWT Middleware):\n- `AuthManager` - RSA public key management from env `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`\n- `AuthMiddleware` - JWT validation (RS256) with Bearer token\n- Key rotation via SIGHUP signal\n- Configurable issuer/audience validation\n- Public path support\n\n### Test Results: ✅ All Passing (28 tests)\n\nThe JWT middleware implementation is complete and tested:\n- Token validation (valid, expired, malformed)\n- Public key loading from PEM\n- Key rotation watcher\n- Issuer/audience validation\n- Body size limits\n\n### Recommendation:\nThe spec file `deployment/client-go.md` appears to be **incorrect** for this AR. The correct spec for AR-017 (PicoD JWT 中间件) should describe the JWT middleware implementation, not a Kubernetes client library.","time":{"start":1775857444653,"end":1775857444653}}}
